news.title: Delhi civic body passes proposal on properties 'booked' for action
news.para: An official later said "booking" refers to a property getting "booked for action" and, if an alteration or addition to an existing building is found violative of the approved building plan, the "illegal part" is marked for demolition.

news.title: Lucknow: Properties of Rohtas Project's owner worth 18.5 crore to be confiscated
news.para: A preliminary order of confiscation was passed in favour of the state under Section 14 (1) of the Uttar Pradesh Gangster and Anti-Social Activities (Prevention) Act 1986.

news.title: Home prices in Hong Kong fall by 1.6% in January 2024
news.para: Home prices in one of the world's most expensive property markets dropped 1.6% last month from the previous month, the ninth monthly fall in a row, official data showed on Tuesday, following a revised 1.5% decline in December.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government pulls up four authorities for delaying affordable housing projects
news.para: The authorities governing Hapur-Pilkhuwa, Unnao-Shuklaganj, Kanpur and Ghaziabad have been asked to expedite work on creating the housing units which have been approved by the central sanctioning and monitoring committee (CSMC).

news.title: LTI Mindtree takes another six lakh sq ft space in Chennai
news.para: In 2023, technology firms LTI Mindtree and L&T Technology Services (LTTS) consolidated their real estate portfolio across Chennai amidst cost-cutting and hybrid work models implemented across sectors.

news.title: Telangana government to regularise unauthorised plots under LRS
news.para: The Congress government in Hyderabad has decided to regularise plots in unauthorised layouts under the Layout Regularisation Scheme introduced by the previous government. Applicants have until March 31 to regularise their plots.

news.title: Niranjan Hiranandani says has heart disorder; got no summons: Group
news.para: “All details were provided to ED and further details shall be provided. We will continue to cooperate fully,” said the spokesperson, who also rebutted rumours of the builder and Darshan being Cyprus citizens.

news.title: Illegal colonies taken over by Gurugram civic body, time now to lay water network & tiles
news.para: Officials said pipelines with 100mm diameter and interlocking tiles with 80mm thickness will be laid in Ryan Enclave, Saraswati Enclave, Bhoop Nagar and Peer Baba colony.

news.title: Gurugram: Expressway Towers buyers protest at Haryana RERA office
news.para: For last two years, the allottees have been demanding action against the developer for its failure to comply with the terms and conditions of licence issued for the project.

news.title: A housing shortage is testing Oregon's pioneering land use law; lawmakers are poised to tweak it
news.para: The so-called urban growth boundary, a sacred cow of Oregon's liberal politics, helped to cement the state's green reputation and has been "extremely influential" in its development, said Megan Horst, an urban planning professor at Portland State University.

news.title: UK builders and government need to fix housing shortage, says regulator
news.para: "Housebuilding in Great Britain needs significant intervention so that enough good quality homes are delivered in the places that people need them," Competition and Markets Authority (CMA) Chief Executive Sarah Cardell said.

news.title: Sagar Cement to divest upto 5% equity share in Andhra Cements
news.para: "Sagar Cements Limited, promoter of the company has conveyed to us its intention to sell the equity shares to enable us to comply with the requirements of minimum public shareholding," Andhra Cements informed in the regulatory filing.

news.title: Shree Cement receives income tax demand of Rs 261 crore
news.para: Shree Cement in the regulatory filing said that the assessment order was received on February 24, 2024 passed under section 143(3) of Income Tax Act, 1961, pertaining to AY 2021-22, wherein certain additions/disallowances have been made.

news.title: Construction sites in Mumbai made to cough up Rs 83 lakh for pollution
news.para: While 1,572 work sites were levied a penalty of Rs 48 lakh for not keeping their premises clean, 139 sites were fined for burning garbage and 537 individuals for unauthorised dumping of construction and demolition (C&D) waste.

news.title: Kalamassery: 30 houses to be built under 'Snehaveedu'
news.para: Addressing the media here on Saturday, industries minister P Rajeeve said 25 of the 30 houses would be constructed for the families of widows.

news.title: Assess & pay property tax online from next month: Patna civic body
news.para: Patna Municipal Corporation (PMC) has decided to launch ‘identification, assessment, payment and property ID generation (IAPP)’ facility for property owners.

news.title: Odisha extends PMAY-Urban 100-day challenge till end of March
news.para: The department had in November 24, 2023 launched the challenge and decided to reward the best performing ULBs for grounding housing projects under PMAY-U.

news.title: Collect property tax on carpet area only: Karnataka home-owners' plea
news.para: The draft notification issued recently has stated that property tax will be calculated based on the guidance value of the property per square feet per year.
